      <article language="en">
        <title locale="en_US">&lt;i&gt;Thienemannimyia &lt;/i&gt;Fittkau (Diptera: Chironomidae) from China</title>
        <abstract locale="en_US">The genus &lt;i&gt;Thienemannimyia&lt;/i&gt; Fittkau, 1957 is recorded from the Oriental region for the first time. &lt;i&gt;T.&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i&gt;barberi&lt;/i&gt; (Coquillett, 1902), &lt;i&gt;T.&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i&gt;fusciceps&lt;/i&gt; (Edwards, 1929) and &lt;i&gt;T.&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i&gt;laeta&lt;/i&gt; (Meigen, 1818) are reported in the region, and two new species, &lt;i&gt;T.&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i&gt;dimorpha&lt;/i&gt; &lt;b&gt;sp.&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;n.&lt;/b&gt; and &lt;i&gt;T.&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i&gt;galbina&lt;/i&gt; &lt;b&gt;sp.&lt;/b&gt; &lt;b&gt;n.&lt;/b&gt; are described and illustrated as males. &lt;i&gt;T.&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i&gt;fusciceps&lt;/i&gt; and &lt;i&gt;T.&lt;/i&gt; &lt;i&gt;geijskesi&lt;/i&gt; (Goetghebuer, 1934) are also recorded from Palaearctic China. The generic diagnosis is emended and a key to the males of &lt;i&gt;Thienemannimyia&lt;/i&gt; is presented.</abstract>
